OL,3,CRed flags on Guernsey's coastal paths
OL,4,Cmark out unique ant nests
OL,6,Fresidents and visitors will start
OL,7,Fseeing red flags along the island's
OL,8,Fsouth coastal path to signify the
OL,9,Fnests of a declining ant species.
OL,11,FDuring the spring, black-backed meadow
OL,12,Fants - scientifically known as Formica
OL,13,Fpratensis - nest in the grassland and
OL,14,Fheathland of the island's cliff faces.
OL,16,FHowever, they can easily be overlooked
OL,17,Fand be put in danger by passers-by and
OL,18,Fstrimmers.
