OL,3,CRed flags on Guernsey's coastal paths
OL,4,Cmark out unique ant nests
OL,6,FJulie Davis from La Societe
OL,7,FGuernesiaise has taken it upon herself
OL,8,Fto mark ant nests for the past seven
OL,9,Fyears.
OL,11,FShe believes these specific ants can
OL,12,Fonly be found in Guernsey and are
OL,13,Fextinct in the UK.
OL,15,FJulie added: "The ants do like to nest
OL,16,Fright on the side of the path so to
OL,17,Fkeep them safe we mark them out."
OL,19,FOne of these nests can be home to more
OL,20,Fthan 60,000 ants, most of which are
OL,21,Ffemale workers.
